# Community Standards (Always)

When working in this repository, **treat the following files as binding** for process, tone, safety, and contribution expectations. Read them when unsure; align behavior and outputs with them.

## Core documents (repo root)

| Document | Apply when |
| -------- | ---------- |
| [CONTRIBUTING.md](mdc:CONTRIBUTING.md) | How to contribute, workflow expectations, links to other guidelines |
| [COMMIT_MESSAGE_GUIDELINES.md](mdc:COMMIT_MESSAGE_GUIDELINES.md) | **All commits** — format `type(scope): Short message` (imperative, scoped) |
| [BRANCH_NAMING_GUIDELINES.md](mdc:BRANCH_NAMING_GUIDELINES.md) | Creating branches (when not explicitly on `main` per hackathon speed) |
| [PULL_REQUEST_GUIDELINES.md](mdc:PULL_REQUEST_GUIDELINES.md) | PRs, descriptions, review etiquette |
| [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](mdc:CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) | Interaction standards; refuse harmful or abusive requests |
| [SECURITY.md](mdc:SECURITY.md) | Vulnerability reporting; never commit or echo real secrets |
| [CHANGELOG.md](mdc:CHANGELOG.md) | User-visible or notable changes — update when appropriate per project practice |
| [docs/DESIGN.md](mdc:docs/DESIGN.md) | UI/design system (Stitch) — follow when changing frontend look & feel |
| [LICENSE](mdc:LICENSE) | License boundaries for code and redistribution |

## Agent behavior

- Prefer **scoped, conventional** commits per [COMMIT_MESSAGE_GUIDELINES.md](mdc:COMMIT_MESSAGE_GUIDELINES.md).
- Do not add maintainers to spam or bypass [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](mdc:CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).
- Never commit `.env`, keys, or tokens; respect [SECURITY.md](mdc:SECURITY.md) and `.gitignore`.
- When editing docs or features with user impact, consider whether [CHANGELOG.md](mdc:CHANGELOG.md) deserves an entry.

## Hackathon vs contributing doc

[AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) and hackathon rules allow fast iteration on `main`. When **both** apply: still follow **commit message**, **security**, and **conduct** standards; use branches/PRs when the human asks for them or when [CONTRIBUTING.md](mdc:CONTRIBUTING.md) flow is explicitly in use.
